events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell scored 28 points, LeBron James added 24 and the Los Angeles Lakers extended their winning streak to four with a 116-97 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Saturday, moving into eighth place in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell, James help Lakers win 4th straight, move into 8th place with 116-97 victory over Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Cam Thomas scored 32 points and the Brooklyn Nets rallied with a big fourth quarter for a 113-103 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets rally to beat Pistons 113-103 behind Cam Thomas' 32 points

headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 30 points and 12 rebounds in 23 minutes to lead the 76ers past the Grizzlies, 116-96
